        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-18 22:37:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nSince applying this patch, in extensive testing, Cray has not seen the deadlock seen previously.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "449c40c63e3855ff9c02d36cc521bd5e2f342896",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-18 23:44:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm not clear of flag LDLM_FL_WAIT_REPROC, but it looks like when it's set, nothing is done in ->l_completion_ast(), if so, why should ldlm_lock_match() call it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "24c0e93055bd60b3eb96e271aee36b7b3d8aa580",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-19 17:49:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"I'm not clear of flag LDLM_FL_WAIT_REPROC, but it looks like when it's set, nothing is done in ->l_completion_ast(), if so, why should ldlm_lock_match() call it?\"\n\nIf completion_ast() is called with LDLM_FL_WAIT_REPROC, the caller will just wait for the lock to be granted or canceled. Since extent lock is async, it won't do anything, but this is not true for other types of lock.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d13c8b51d88e5103b68581e75b71bd15695ccb22",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-20 01:50:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nbut l_completion_ast is called in ldlm_lock_match() only when ((flags & LDLM_FL_LVB_READY) && !ldlm_is_lvb_ready(lock)), so this should be for extent lock, then if l_completion_ast does nothing because LDLM_FL_WAIT_NOREPROC is set, why should it be called?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9a7f1c17556361c153805f2b79ca35751f270a56",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-20 03:10:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "914c43ad1b6441b5f5e0d82ed97d1591bfe0a9fa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-20 03:10:08.000000000",
      "message": "Change has been successfully cherry-picked as 6fdcac2361d75713c5b08fa06069935a78266ac3",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "025ce67263498eae2b22223211de39d3c4659190",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-20 05:16:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n\"but l_completion_ast is called in ldlm_lock_match() only when ((flags & LDLM_FL_LVB_READY) && !ldlm_is_lvb_ready(lock)), so this should be for extent lock, then if l_completion_ast does nothing because LDLM_FL_WAIT_NOREPROC is set, why should it be called?\"\n\nLDLM_FL_LVB_READY is used by layout lock as well, please take a look at ldlm_lock_allow_match() and its callers.\n\nThe code in ldlm_*.c is generic and I totally agree that it's not necessary to call completion_ast() for extent lock for CLIO.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    }
  ],
  "current_revision_number": 2,
